Driver, who was fired at 210 km / h and hot drink between your legs, receives £ 1,000 fine
A motorist was imposed a penalty of £ 1,000, because he had driven up to 210 km / h and a hot drink between his legs.
Andrew Howie, 35, from Tiptree, Essex, on 27 May his Mercedes Benz on the A120 at Braintree stopped.
After it had stopped the police, they discovered the beverage cup between his legs.
Before the district court Colchester to Howie pleaded guilty to be driven without due care and attention.
He received seven points and a six-month driving ban.
Howie was also to pay costs of £ 90 and a victim surcharge convicted of £ 100.
